text: Wycombe Abbey is a private secondary boarding school for girls in High Wycombe, England. It has one of the best girls' boarding school exam results in the United Kingdom. 37% of students go on to Oxford or Cambridge universities. It was started in 1896 by Dame Frances Gove. The headmistress is Rhiannon Wilkinson. It costs Â£11,100 per term for boarders. All girls year 79 have to learn Latin. It is a Church of England school with its own chapel. ==References== Category:Schools in Buckinghamshire Category:1896 establishments in England
